<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f101015369989863>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: The Halfling Rogue</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jan 4th 9:14 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1160 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>For untwinked rogues here is what you should get:<br><br>Leather Armor and a shield until you get dual weild.&nbsp;&nbsp;Work your way up to banded.  <br><br>For weapons, I recommend a Giant Snake Fang. they are a common drop off most large snakes and asps. You could probably find one at a vendor for 1pp or less.  It is a decent piercing weapon until your mid-teens.  <br><br>Until you get backstab at level 10, you are really just another tank but with no kick or bash. After level 10 your tactics change slightly since you now have backstab.  But at that level it is unreliable.  Mostly just an extra melee attack. But be patient.  The best is yet to come.<br><br>By level 12 you should get a magic piercing weapon.  Dragoon Dirk, Bloodstained Fang, or Walrus Tooth should do.<br><br>Then hunt Willowisps. You can backstab them and pick pocket them even though they don't have backs or pockets. Trust me. You will get money. You will spend it. You will get experience. You will level quickly.<br><br>By mid teens you should have been able to buy a full suite of banded armor (about 60pp). Banded will last you into your mid 20's. Supplement it with Blackenend Alloy armor as you can find/buy/steal it.  Then get Ravenscale or Ry'Gor as you can afford it. The shield should be replaced by a secondary weapon of your choice. Your primary weapon should always be a piercer (since only piercing weapons can backstab).  For a good weapon you can afford by level 18 or so try to acquire a crystal grinder for your primary. I have been using one for 12 levels now with no complaints. A slime coated harpoon is better but costs at least 4 times as much on the open market.  Everything I have mentioned so far is under 500pp (most under 200pp) except for the Ravenscale and Ry'Gor Breastplates which are about 800p.<br><br>Rogues don't get really good quests at low level (unless you're a barbarian then you can quest for black wolf hide armor).  Wood Elves and Half Elves that start in Kelethin can do the scout dagger and scout cape/leggings quest. <br><br>One more hint:  Should you choose to take up the fine art of poisoning you should learn pottery, also.  Save every zombie skin you find.  They are a component in making poison vials. You don't have to use zombie skins but they are light weight and stackable so you can carry a lot without getting encumbered.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></tr>
